parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident. The recall issues and lack of available parts can cause delays in repairing the vehicle, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminated
airbag did not deploy in an accident
airbag deployed late
injuries sustained due to airbag failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal does not return to normal position
inability to stop the vehicle
accidents caused by brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships and manufacturers to address recall issues and provide adequate support can lead to delays in repairing the vehicle, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Dealership refuses to do recall
manufacturer does not provide available parts
lack of communication from dealership and manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel pump shuts off
gasoline spills out of the tank
the fuel gauge is inaccurate
the vehicle will not take fuel
and the fuel tank will not fill completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body or acceleration system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates while braking
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
and the engine dies while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system fails
the ignition starter sticks
and the vehicle's computer system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without the driver's input
and may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking throttle body or accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck or stuck in a position
causing the engine to rev excessively or the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic throttle control issues can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The electronic throttle control system malfunctions
causing the engine to rev excessively or the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably.
